Concerning network speeds in the last posts... your "10 megabyte" connection is probably a 10 megabit connection = 1.25 megabytes. 1 byte = 8 bits.

Almost any wireless connection will tell you the speed is 54 megabits but that is just between you and the router.

Some ISPs do their best to limit bandwidth for p2p/torrents, but generally forwarding a port in your router to your computer for the torrent client helps speeds as someone said.
